<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><!DOCTYPE article  PUBLIC '-//OASIS//DTD DocBook XML V4.4//EN'  'http://www.docbook.org/xml/4.4/docbookx.dtd'><article><articleinfo><title>ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem</title><revhistory><revision><revnumber>4</revnumber><date>2010-07-09 07:20:10</date><authorinitials>FrancescoChemolli</authorinitials><revremark>Fixed some broken links</revremark></revision><revision><revnumber>3</revnumber><date>2010-07-07 02:16:58</date><authorinitials>AmosJeffries</authorinitials><revremark>SMP in 3.2 now deprecates this particular config. new examples needed for that later.</revremark></revision><revision><revnumber>2</revnumber><date>2009-03-06 16:47:28</date><authorinitials>FrancescoChemolli</authorinitials><revremark>added configuration file samples</revremark></revision><revision><revnumber>1</revnumber><date>2009-03-06 16:35:13</date><authorinitials>FrancescoChemolli</authorinitials><revremark>initial version.</revremark></revision></revhistory></articleinfo><section><title>MultiCpuSystem</title><para><emphasis role="strong">Warning</emphasis>: Any example presented here is provided &quot;as-is&quot; with no support or guarantee of suitability. If you have any further questions about these examples please email the squid-users mailing list. </para><itemizedlist><listitem override="none"><para><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata depth="15" fileref="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/wiki/squidtheme/img/alert.png" width="15"/></imageobject><textobject><phrase>/!\</phrase></textobject></inlinemediaobject> <inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata depth="16" fileref="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/wiki/squidtheme/img/icon-info.png" width="16"/></imageobject><textobject><phrase>{i}</phrase></textobject></inlinemediaobject> <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/Squid-3.2#">Squid-3.2</ulink> has now had experimental multi-process SMP support merged. It is designed to operate with a similar but different configuration to these while reducing much of the complexity of process instance management. </para></listitem></itemizedlist><section><title>Outline</title><para>Squid-3.1 and older do not scale very well to Multi-CPU or Multi-Core systems. Some of its features do help, such as for example <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/Features/DiskDaemon#">DiskDaemon</ulink>, or <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/Features/CyclicObjectStorageSystem#">COSS</ulink>, or the ability to delegate parts of the request processing to external helpers such as <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/SquidFaq/ProxyAuthentication#">Authenticators</ulink> or <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/SquidFaq/RelatedSoftware#">other auxiliary software</ulink>. Still Squid remains to this day very bound to a single processing core model. There are plans to eventually make Squid able to effectively use multicore systems, but something may be done already, by using a fine-tuned <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/MultipleInstances#">MultipleInstances</ulink> setup. </para><informaltable><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col_0"/><colspec colname="col_1"/><tbody><row rowsep="1"><entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para> <inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata depth="15" fileref="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/wiki/squidtheme/img/alert.png" width="15"/></imageobject><textobject><phrase>/!\</phrase></textobject></inlinemediaobject> Notice </para></entry><entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para> This setup has been designed with a recent version of Squid in mind. It has been tested with <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/Squid-3.1#">Squid-3.1</ulink>, but it should work with <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/Squid-3.0#">Squid-3.0</ulink> and <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/Squid-2.7#">Squid-2.7</ulink> as-is as well. <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/Squid-2.6#">Squid-2.6</ulink> and earlier can be coaxed to work, but it will be harder to setup and maintain. </para></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></informaltable><para>It is also geared at <emphasis role="strong">expert system-administrators</emphasis>. <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/MultipleInstances#">MultipleInstances</ulink> is not easy to manage and run, and system integration depends on the specific details of the operating system distribution of choice. </para><para>The setup laid out in this <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/ConfigExamples#">configuration example</ulink> aims at creating on a system multiple running squid processes: </para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>a 'front-end' process which does </para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>authentication </para></listitem><listitem><para>authorization </para></listitem><listitem><para>logging, delay pools etc. </para></listitem><listitem><para>in-memory hot-object caching </para></listitem><listitem><para>load-balancing of the backend processes </para></listitem><listitem><para>redirection etc. </para></listitem></itemizedlist></listitem><listitem><para>a 'back-end' processes farm, whose each does </para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>disk caching </para></listitem><listitem><para>do the network heavy lifting </para></listitem></itemizedlist></listitem></itemizedlist><para>While this setup is expected to increase the general throughput of a multicore system, the benefits are anyways constrained, as the frontend process is still expected to be the bottleneck. Should anyone put this in production, he's encouraged to share the results to help others evaluate the effectiveness of the solution. </para></section><section><title>Squid Configuration File</title><para>For a 2-backends system, there are 5 configuration files to be used. You can click below each file on its filename to download it, no need to copy and paste. The .txt extension an artifact, please remove it. </para><section><title>acl</title><para>This file contains the ACL's that are common to all running instances. This allows to change cluster-wide parameters without needing to touch each instance's. Each instance will still have to be reconfigured individually. <programlisting format="linespecific" language="highlight" linenumbering="numbered" startinglinenumber="1"><![CDATA[acl manager proto cache_object]]>
<![CDATA[acl localhost src 127.0.0.1/32]]>
<![CDATA[acl to_localhost dst 127.0.0.0/8]]>
<![CDATA[acl localnet src 192.168.0.0/24]]>
<![CDATA[acl SSL_ports port 443]]>
<![CDATA[acl Safe_ports port 80      # http]]>
<![CDATA[acl Safe_ports port 21      # ftp]]>
<![CDATA[acl Safe_ports port 443     # https]]>
<![CDATA[acl Safe_ports port 70      # gopher]]>
<![CDATA[acl Safe_ports port 210     # wais]]>
<![CDATA[acl Safe_ports port 1025-65535  # unregistered ports]]>
<![CDATA[acl Safe_ports port 280     # http-mgmt]]>
<![CDATA[acl Safe_ports port 488     # gss-http]]>
<![CDATA[acl Safe_ports port 591     # filemaker]]>
<![CDATA[acl Safe_ports port 777     # multiling http]]>
<![CDATA[acl CONNECT method CONNECT]]>



<![CDATA[cachemgr_passwd somepassword all]]>
</programlisting><ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem?action=AttachFile&amp;do=get&amp;target=common.acl.conf.txt">common.acl.conf.txt</ulink> </para></section><section><title>common backend parameters</title><para>Backends share most of the configuration, it makes sense to also join those <programlisting format="linespecific" language="highlight" linenumbering="numbered" startinglinenumber="1"><![CDATA[#you want the backend to have a small cache_mem]]>
<![CDATA[cache_mem 4 MB]]>

<![CDATA[refresh_pattern ^ftp:		1440	20%	10080]]>
<![CDATA[refresh_pattern ^gopher:	1440	0%	1440]]>
<![CDATA[refresh_pattern -i (/cgi-bin/|\?) 0	0%	0]]>
<![CDATA[refresh_pattern .		0	20%	4320]]>

<![CDATA[shutdown_lifetime 3 second]]>
<![CDATA[#debug_options all,8]]>

<![CDATA[# add user authentication and similar options]]>
<![CDATA[http_access deny !Safe_ports]]>
<![CDATA[http_access deny CONNECT !SSL_ports]]>
<![CDATA[http_access allow localhost]]>
<![CDATA[http_access deny all]]>
</programlisting><ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem?action=AttachFile&amp;do=get&amp;target=common.backend.conf.txt">common.backend.conf.txt</ulink> </para></section><section><title>frontend</title><para><programlisting format="linespecific" language="highlight" linenumbering="numbered" startinglinenumber="1"><![CDATA[# acl are shared among instances]]>
<![CDATA[include /usr/local/etc/lab/common.acl.conf]]>

<![CDATA[http_port 3128]]>

<![CDATA[#add backends]]>
<![CDATA[cache_peer localhost parent 4001 0 carp login=PASS name=backend-1]]>
<![CDATA[cache_peer localhost parent 4002 0 carp login=PASS name=backend-2]]>

<![CDATA[#you want the frontend to have a significant cache_mem]]>
<![CDATA[cache_mem 512 MB]]>

<![CDATA[refresh_pattern ^ftp:		1440	20%	10080]]>
<![CDATA[refresh_pattern ^gopher:	1440	0%	1440]]>
<![CDATA[refresh_pattern -i (/cgi-bin/|\?) 0	0%	0]]>
<![CDATA[refresh_pattern .		0	20%	4320]]>

<![CDATA[shutdown_lifetime 3 second]]>
<![CDATA[#debug_options all,8]]>

<![CDATA[# change /tmp to your own log directory, e.g. /var/log/squid]]>
<![CDATA[access_log /var/log/squid/frontend.access.log]]>
<![CDATA[cache_log /var/log/squid/frontend.cache.log]]>
<![CDATA[pid_filename /var/log/squid/frontend.pid]]>

<![CDATA[# add user authentication and similar options]]>
<![CDATA[http_access allow manager localhost]]>
<![CDATA[http_access deny manager]]>
<![CDATA[http_access deny !Safe_ports]]>
<![CDATA[http_access deny CONNECT !SSL_ports]]>
<![CDATA[http_access allow localnet]]>
<![CDATA[http_access allow localhost]]>
<![CDATA[http_access deny all]]>
</programlisting><ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem?action=AttachFile&amp;do=get&amp;target=frontend.conf.txt">frontend.conf.txt</ulink> </para></section><section><title>backend 1</title><para><programlisting format="linespecific" language="highlight" linenumbering="numbered" startinglinenumber="1"><![CDATA[# acl are shared among instances]]>
<![CDATA[include /usr/local/etc/lab/common.acl.conf]]>

<![CDATA[http_port 127.0.0.1:4001]]>
<![CDATA[visible_hostname backend-1]]>
<![CDATA[unique_hostname backend-1]]>
<![CDATA[cache_dir aufs /mnt/cache-1 10240 128 128]]>

<![CDATA[# change /var/log/squid to your own log directory]]>
<![CDATA[access_log /var/log/squid/backend-1.access.log]]>
<![CDATA[cache_log /var/log/squid/backend-1.cache.log]]>
<![CDATA[pid_filename /var/log/squid/backend-1.pid]]>

<![CDATA[include /usr/local/etc/lab/common.backend.conf]]>
</programlisting><ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem?action=AttachFile&amp;do=get&amp;target=backend-1.conf.txt">backend-1.conf.txt</ulink> </para></section><section><title>backend 2</title><para><programlisting format="linespecific" language="highlight" linenumbering="numbered" startinglinenumber="1"><![CDATA[# acl are shared among instances]]>
<![CDATA[include /usr/local/etc/lab/common.acl.conf]]>

<![CDATA[http_port 127.0.0.1:4002]]>
<![CDATA[visible_hostname backend-2]]>
<![CDATA[unique_hostname backend-2]]>
<![CDATA[cache_dir aufs /mnt/cache-2 10240 128 128]]>

<![CDATA[# change /var/log/squid to your own log directory]]>
<![CDATA[access_log /var/log/squid/backend-2.access.log]]>
<![CDATA[cache_log /var/log/squid/backend-2.cache.log]]>
<![CDATA[pid_filename /var/log/squid/backend-2.pid]]>

<![CDATA[include /usr/local/etc/lab/common.backend.conf]]>
</programlisting><ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem?action=AttachFile&amp;do=get&amp;target=backend-2.conf.txt">backend-2.conf.txt</ulink> </para><!--rule (<hr>) is not applicable to DocBook--><para> <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ConfigExamples/MultiCpuSystem/CategoryConfigExample#">CategoryConfigExample</ulink> </para></section></section></section></article>